# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version if you're
#   using pyenv, but library authors might not want to.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if used with a poweruser option, the lockfile may be
#   customized.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock contains the resolved dependencies.
#   It's recommended to commit this file in applications, but maybe not libraries.
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock contains the resolved dependencies.
#pdm.lock

